    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="96"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d96">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5445</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1917</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1420. Diplomatic Commission given hearty welcome this afternoon by Russo-American
                    committee. Speeches made by representatives of Government and by representatives
                    of twelve municipalities and commercial organizations, also by <persName
                        corresp="#p_RE1">Root</persName> and myself. Commission going Moscow
                    to-night.</p>
                <p>Railway Commission working diligently. Will meet Minister Ways Communications at
                    Embassy evening 22d. <persName corresp="#p_SJF1">Stevens</persName> improving
                    but slowly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_FDR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
